    "TSF is better than DrCIF on just 6 of the 112 datasets absence.",
    "To evaluate a shapelet, the subseries is slid across the time series, and the z-normalised Euclidean distance between the shapelet and the underlying window is calculated.",
    "The distance between a shapelet and any series, s Dist, is the minimum distance over all such windows.",
    "Figure 16 shows a visualisation of the s Dist process.",
    "The shapelet S is shifted along the time series A, and the most similar offset and distance in A are recorded."
